WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:01:38.475 --> 00:01:39.475
Prego.

3
00:01:46.308 --> 00:01:49.141
- Pronto.
- Is this Dr. Martins?

4
00:01:49.225 --> 00:01:50.475
Yes. this is Dr. Martins.

5
00:01:50.559 --> 00:01:53.016
- Who is this?
- NASA Space Biosciences Research.

6
00:01:53.100 --> 00:01:54.141
We're patching through your call.

7
00:01:54.225 --> 00:01:55.058
My call? I...

8
00:01:55.141 --> 00:01:57.642
Hello? Who is it now?
Why can't I talk

9
00:01:57.725 --> 00:01:59.767
- to the same person?
- Hello. this is Dr. Martins.

10
00:01:59.850 --> 00:02:01.308
- Oh. please!
- Who is this?

11
00:02:01.392 --> 00:02:03.016
Something came out of your tank!

12
00:02:03.100 --> 00:02:04.517
Okay. slow down.
Can you tell me

13
00:02:04.600 --> 00:02:06.183
- your name. please. sir?
- I told the man!

14
00:02:06.267 --> 00:02:08.725
I told them all!
Six times I've called already!

15
00:02:08.809 --> 00:02:11.559
Always a different person!
Where am I calling now?

16
00:02:11.642 --> 00:02:14.684
Rome. I'm a research microbiologist
at Sapienza.

17
00:02:14.767 --> 00:02:17.016
- Oh. why'd they give me you?
- I...

18
00:02:17.100 --> 00:02:20.433
I consult for NASA sometimes.
epidemiological surveillance.

19
00:02:20.517 --> 00:02:22.517
Now it's your turn.
Who are you. sir?

20
00:02:22.600 --> 00:02:24.100
Enos Minjarra.

21
00:02:24.892 --> 00:02:26.517
I live in Kiwirrkurra.

22
00:02:26.600 --> 00:02:27.892
Kiwirrkurra. where is that?

23
00:02:28.392 --> 00:02:29.850
We're dying!

24
00:02:29.933 --> 00:02:32.725
We're all dying!
Something came out of your tank!

25
00:02:32.809 --> 00:02:36.016
- What tank?
- The one uncle found. near Tanami Basin.

26
00:02:36.100 --> 00:02:39.850
- Australia?
- Yes. long time ago. in the '70s!

27
00:02:40.392 --> 00:02:41.642
But now. something came out.

28
00:02:41.725 --> 00:02:44.600
and if you're NASA.
this is your tank!

29
00:02:44.684 --> 00:02:46.350
You have to help us!

30
00:02:47.100 --> 00:02:48.308
Where did the tank come from?

31
00:02:48.392 --> 00:02:50.183
Where did it come from...

32
00:02:50.267 --> 00:02:51.767
- Hello?
- Are you still there?

33
00:02:51.850 --> 00:02:52.933
- Hello...
- Sir...

34
00:02:53.016 --> 00:02:54.350
Taxi!

35
00:02:54.433 --> 00:02:55.933
Can you hear me. sir?

36
00:02:56.016 --> 00:02:58.141
I can't hear you.

37
00:03:02.183 --> 00:03:04.600
Help us.

38
00:03:33.308 --> 00:03:36.350
Dr. Hero Martins.
Major Robert Quinn.

39
00:03:37.100 --> 00:03:38.100
DTRA.

40
00:03:39.100 --> 00:03:41.767
This is my partner.
Lieutenant Colonel Trini Romano.

41
00:03:41.849 --> 00:03:43.767
How are ya?

42
00:03:43.849 --> 00:03:45.600
Where's the rest of your team?

43
00:03:45.684 --> 00:03:46.849
You're looking at us.

44
00:03:49.141 --> 00:03:51.225
Okay. let's get started.

45
00:03:52.684 --> 00:03:56.767
I thought the Skylab Space Station
fell in the Indian Ocean in '79.

46
00:03:56.849 --> 00:03:58.975
Well. most of it did.

47
00:03:59.058 --> 00:04:00.849
but when it broke up
in the atmosphere.

48
00:04:00.933 --> 00:04:03.475
one of the O2 tanks
was recovered near here.

49
00:04:03.559 --> 00:04:05.600
Some guy found it.
put it in front of his house.

50
00:04:05.684 --> 00:04:07.308
thought people might pay
to come see it.

51
00:04:07.392 --> 00:04:09.267
Just an empty oxygen tank?

52
00:04:09.350 --> 00:04:10.975
No. this one wasn't empty.

53
00:04:11.058 --> 00:04:13.058
It was sent up
with a microbial organism.

54
00:04:13.141 --> 00:04:16.308
a parasitic fungus that could adapt
from one species to another.

55
00:04:16.392 --> 00:04:19.308
So. we sent up a terrestrial fungus
and it came back down.

56
00:04:19.392 --> 00:04:20.849
- What's the problem?
- The problem is.

57
00:04:20.933 --> 00:04:23.517
I think what went into the tank
is not what came out.

58
00:04:24.517 --> 00:04:27.725
And now. everyone in Kiwirrkurra is dying.
Or dead.

59
00:04:27.808 --> 00:04:30.141
No one has been in or out
since that phone call.

60
00:04:35.891 --> 00:04:37.642
- Epinephrine. yeah?
- Yeah.

61
00:04:37.725 --> 00:04:40.100
I would rather not discover
a lethal allergen the hard way.

62
00:04:45.100 --> 00:04:48.308
- When were you first notified?
- Less than 30 hours ago.

63
00:04:48.392 --> 00:04:51.058
- So. when did the outbreak start?
- That's unclear.

64
00:04:52.100 --> 00:04:53.975
Have you been called
for this sort of thing before?

65
00:04:54.058 --> 00:04:55.975
Space shit?
Oh. all the time.

66
00:04:56.600 --> 00:04:58.725
- Robert.
- Sorry. No.

67
00:04:59.267 --> 00:05:01.225
Bioweapons and nuclear threats. yes.

68
00:05:01.308 --> 00:05:03.600
Extraterrestrials. no.

69
00:05:03.684 --> 00:05:06.725
Why would they intentionally send
a hazardous organism into space?

70
00:05:06.808 --> 00:05:10.891
Research? To develop
an antifungal medication for astronauts.

71
00:05:11.517 --> 00:05:12.684
Switching bodycams on.

72
00:05:29.933 --> 00:05:31.183
A suitcase.

73
00:05:32.849 --> 00:05:35.350
- Somebody tried to leave.
- Or they arrived.

74
00:05:35.849 --> 00:05:39.058
Maybe people come from all over Australia
just to stay here.

75
00:05:39.141 --> 00:05:42.350
<i>And I am the light.</i>

76
00:05:42.433 --> 00:05:46.100
<i>He who believes in me shall rejoice.</i>

77
00:05:46.183 --> 00:05:47.975
<i>It shall be...</i>

78
00:05:51.475 --> 00:05:55.392
Fourteen houses. 12 cars.
and no people.

79
00:05:56.642 --> 00:05:58.600
So. where the hell is everybody?

80
00:06:07.475 --> 00:06:10.267
I found it! Over here.

81
00:06:22.559 --> 00:06:23.891
Here we go.

82
00:06:24.475 --> 00:06:26.016
We don't know
what we're dealing with.

83
00:06:26.100 --> 00:06:28.183
Don't touch the tank.
Stay behind me.

84
00:06:42.975 --> 00:06:44.308
It's a folkloric solution.

85
00:06:45.100 --> 00:06:46.683
potatoes and dish soap.

86
00:06:46.766 --> 00:06:48.267
The guy must've been trying to clean it.

87
00:06:58.016 --> 00:07:00.267
Microfissures in the tank.

88
00:07:00.350 --> 00:07:04.475
polysaccharide in the potato.
sodium palmitate in the soap.

89
00:07:04.559 --> 00:07:06.350
Dripped into the tank.
it's protein rich.

90
00:07:07.724 --> 00:07:08.891
The guy might not have meant to.

91
00:07:08.975 --> 00:07:10.891
but he created one hell
of a pro-growth environment.

92
00:07:10.975 --> 00:07:13.683
All it needs is some water
and it would really multiply.

93
00:07:21.933 --> 00:07:23.350
Who the hell are you?

94
00:07:28.891 --> 00:07:29.891
Hey. can you...

95
00:07:30.891 --> 00:07:32.350
just grab the loop in my suit?

96
00:07:33.641 --> 00:07:35.350
- I'm gonna pull against you.
- Yeah?

97
00:07:35.433 --> 00:07:36.641
But just don't let me go. okay?

98
00:07:36.724 --> 00:07:38.517
Yeah. I gotcha.

99
00:07:38.599 --> 00:07:40.559
All right. if I start to fall.
just pull back hard.

100
00:07:40.641 --> 00:07:41.641
Ready?

101
00:07:50.350 --> 00:07:52.559
Jesus Christ.

102
00:07:52.641 --> 00:07:56.141
- What is it?
- I don't know. But it's big. fast.

103
00:07:56.225 --> 00:07:58.016
and it's heterotrophic.

104
00:08:02.141 --> 00:08:03.975
- You okay?
- Yeah. thanks.

105
00:08:04.058 --> 00:08:06.433
Hey! I found a body!

106
00:08:32.267 --> 00:08:34.475
- I've got you.
- Thanks.

107
00:08:47.225 --> 00:08:50.392
Pockmarks in the skin.
erupted flesh...

108
00:08:53.766 --> 00:08:55.100
He... He burst.

109
00:08:55.933 --> 00:08:56.933
You don't say.

110
00:08:57.516 --> 00:08:59.267
Plates of the skull are split.

111
00:08:59.350 --> 00:09:01.225
all eight seamlines.

112
00:09:04.183 --> 00:09:06.641
- Oh. my God.
- What?

113
00:09:08.891 --> 00:09:10.433
It's all of them.

114
00:09:20.975 --> 00:09:23.225
Why the hell
they all climb their roofs?

115
00:09:23.308 --> 00:09:25.474
- It told them to.
- The fungus?

116
00:09:25.558 --> 00:09:29.100
Yes. That's how an insect-pathogenic
fungus reproduces.

117
00:09:29.183 --> 00:09:33.100
It controls all brain function.
movement. reflex. impulse.

118
00:09:33.183 --> 00:09:36.474
It's driven to infect other hosts
any way it can.

119
00:09:37.100 --> 00:09:40.058
Sometimes. it tells them
to climb and wait.

120
00:09:40.141 --> 00:09:42.225
- For what?
- For the fungus to overfill

121
00:09:42.308 --> 00:09:44.975
its body cavity and burst.

122
00:09:45.766 --> 00:09:46.766
And spread.

123
00:09:46.849 --> 00:09:49.100
But that's... that's only insects.

124
00:09:50.808 --> 00:09:52.058
It was.

125
00:09:54.766 --> 00:09:56.267
Jesus!

126
00:09:58.808 --> 00:10:01.308
Get your sample. Doc.
and let's get the hell out of here.

127
00:10:02.933 --> 00:10:04.933
Maybe the tank
picked up a hitchhiker.

128
00:10:05.016 --> 00:10:07.641
maybe a spore penetrated
its shell upon reentry.

129
00:10:07.724 --> 00:10:10.599
but however it happened.

130
00:10:11.516 --> 00:10:13.558
I think we've created a new species.

131
00:10:15.683 --> 00:10:18.891
We need to burn this place.
To the ground. Right away.

132
00:10:18.975 --> 00:10:22.183
A couple M47s loaded with
white phosphorus ought to do the job.

133
00:10:22.267 --> 00:10:24.516
- Yeah.
- That will cover any spread.

134
00:10:37.183 --> 00:10:38.308
Dr. Martins.

135
00:10:38.891 --> 00:10:39.891
Dr. Martins?

136
00:10:40.641 --> 00:10:41.641
Come on. we need to go.

137
00:10:42.516 --> 00:10:43.766
All right. I'm done.

138
00:10:48.891 --> 00:10:49.975
Come on. let's move.

139
00:10:57.766 --> 00:11:00.849
You smell that? Burnt toast?

140
00:11:00.933 --> 00:11:03.350
- In your suit?
- It's not possible.

141
00:11:03.432 --> 00:11:05.849
My suit is sealed and overpressured.
there's nothing in here

142
00:11:05.933 --> 00:11:07.474
but oxygen and clean CO2.

143
00:11:09.058 --> 00:11:10.141
Feel anything?

144
00:11:12.349 --> 00:11:14.683
- A little hot.
- We'll lose the suits at the jeep.

145
00:11:14.766 --> 00:11:17.641
They need to burn here anyway.
We'll check yours for breaches.

146
00:11:18.267 --> 00:11:21.141
Who the hell's gonna store this thing?
CDC?

147
00:11:21.225 --> 00:11:25.183
No. Atlanta and Galveston
will both classify extraterrestrial.

148
00:11:25.267 --> 00:11:26.432
They'll reject it outright.

149
00:11:27.267 --> 00:11:29.058
Fort Detrick?

150
00:11:29.141 --> 00:11:31.558
Still in a top-down review
after their last breach.

151
00:11:31.641 --> 00:11:32.975
I wouldn't trust it to them.

152
00:11:37.100 --> 00:11:38.432
What about Atchison?

153
00:11:39.308 --> 00:11:40.724
What. the mines in Kansas?

154
00:11:40.808 --> 00:11:43.349
Exactly. nobody ever uses them.

155
00:11:44.307 --> 00:11:45.474
Yeah. not bad.

156
00:11:46.432 --> 00:11:47.891
No. No!

157
00:11:48.599 --> 00:11:50.516
Hero? You okay?

158
00:11:50.599 --> 00:11:52.349
Stop! Stop!

159
00:11:52.432 --> 00:11:53.683
Can you hear me?

160
00:12:06.058 --> 00:12:08.849
Spread. spread. spread. spread.

161
00:12:08.933 --> 00:12:10.474
spread. spread. spread!

162
00:12:13.141 --> 00:12:14.933
Hero. can you hear me?

163
00:12:15.016 --> 00:12:17.267
She's infected! Stop!

164
00:12:18.432 --> 00:12:19.432
Stop!

165
00:12:20.474 --> 00:12:21.474
Stop!

166
00:12:27.266 --> 00:12:29.474
I can't move my legs.

167
00:12:30.183 --> 00:12:32.641
Hero! Stop!

168
00:12:32.724 --> 00:12:34.058
Stop!

169
00:12:35.058 --> 00:12:38.058
Hero. no! Listen to me! Stop.

170
00:12:42.724 --> 00:12:45.141
Hero. don't! Don't!
What are you...

171
00:12:45.225 --> 00:12:47.558
No. Hero. Stop.

172
00:12:47.641 --> 00:12:48.808
Put it down. Hero.

173
00:12:48.891 --> 00:12:50.432
Hero. you're infected!

174
00:12:51.933 --> 00:12:53.766
Don't! No. no. no. no!

175
00:12:58.224 --> 00:12:59.933
Oh. God.

176
00:13:01.975 --> 00:13:03.183
Robert.

177
00:13:03.266 --> 00:13:04.266
Robert!

178
00:15:47.724 --> 00:15:50.724
<i>Making the decision
to change your life</i>

179
00:15:51.349 --> 00:15:53.391
<i>is a courageous first step.</i>

180
00:15:54.558 --> 00:15:57.975
<i>Once you're convinced
of the need for change.</i>

181
00:15:58.057 --> 00:16:02.016
<i>some of that courage will need
to be directed outward</i>

182
00:16:02.099 --> 00:16:06.099
<i>into a world that would prefer
you stay exactly as you are.</i>

183
00:16:07.849 --> 00:16:11.349
<i>Dealing with difficult
and confrontational people</i>

184
00:16:11.432 --> 00:16:13.975
<i>is. like many things. a skill</i>

185
00:16:14.641 --> 00:16:16.766
<i>that can be developed over time.</i>

186
00:16:16.849 --> 00:16:20.641
<i>but no change is possible without...</i>

187
00:16:25.015 --> 00:16:26.808
Well. shithead?

188
00:16:28.391 --> 00:16:31.057
I told you. Griffin. can't help you.

189
00:16:31.140 --> 00:16:33.808
I wish I could. but I can't.
Sorry.

190
00:16:33.891 --> 00:16:36.558
I knew you were stupid.
didn't think you were that stupid.

191
00:16:36.641 --> 00:16:39.182
I'm not stupid.

192
00:16:39.266 --> 00:16:41.224
I mean. I... Listen.
I get you're my boss and all.

193
00:16:41.307 --> 00:16:42.474
and I would help you if I could.

194
00:16:42.558 --> 00:16:44.558
but it's messed up for me...

195
00:16:44.641 --> 00:16:47.391
vis-à-vis my. you know.
personal situation.

196
00:16:47.474 --> 00:16:49.432
and I'm not gonna do it.

197
00:16:49.516 --> 00:16:50.974
Okay. so you think about it.

198
00:16:51.599 --> 00:16:53.140
No.
I wish I didn't even know about it.

199
00:16:53.224 --> 00:16:55.057
What's the big goddamn deal?
Nobody's gonna know!

200
00:16:57.724 --> 00:16:59.599
I've heard those words before.

201
00:17:00.933 --> 00:17:03.558
- You do it.
- I don't work nights.

202
00:17:03.641 --> 00:17:05.724
and no one's gonna come
for that shit in the daytime.

203
00:17:05.808 --> 00:17:07.015
- Well.
- So. just let 'em in

204
00:17:07.099 --> 00:17:08.349
so you and me don't have a problem.

205
00:17:08.432 --> 00:17:10.349
Why do we gotta have a problem?

206
00:17:10.432 --> 00:17:13.140
'Cause you know. but you're not in.

207
00:17:13.224 --> 00:17:15.974
and if you're not in and you know.

208
00:17:16.599 --> 00:17:17.933
then we got a problem.

209
00:17:22.349 --> 00:17:23.891
You got the new help tonight.

210
00:17:23.974 --> 00:17:26.266
She's on walk
and lock check till 12:00.

211
00:17:27.015 --> 00:17:28.015
What's her name?

212
00:17:29.140 --> 00:17:30.766
Don't get any ideas.

213
00:17:30.849 --> 00:17:32.391
She's already hitting on me.

214
00:17:37.015 --> 00:17:39.349
Something's beeping in there!
Fix it!

215
00:17:39.432 --> 00:17:41.266
Wait. wha...

216
00:17:42.932 --> 00:17:44.182
Asshole.

217
00:18:20.974 --> 00:18:22.474
<i>Expect heavy rains tonight</i>

218
00:18:22.558 --> 00:18:25.683
<i>with showers starting in the early evening
and intensifying overnight.</i>

219
00:18:25.766 --> 00:18:28.140
<i>Thunderstorms are likely
with strong gusts of wind</i>

220
00:18:28.224 --> 00:18:29.391
<i>and potential local...</i>

221
00:18:37.266 --> 00:18:40.349
Ah. Mrs. Rooney. how's it going?
Staying cool?

222
00:18:40.432 --> 00:18:43.641
I need to get into SB-114.

223
00:18:44.266 --> 00:18:45.890
It's my anniversary.

224
00:18:46.683 --> 00:18:48.641
Ah. okay. Superhot out. right?

225
00:18:48.724 --> 00:18:51.015
Kinda weird this time of year.
but I guess we gotta...

226
00:18:51.099 --> 00:18:52.766
I need to get into it quick.

227
00:18:53.558 --> 00:18:56.808
God. absolutely. Storage emergency.
I totally get it.

228
00:18:56.890 --> 00:18:58.391
It's snowing. it's sunny.

229
00:18:58.474 --> 00:19:00.558
it's raining. it's hot. I...
I don't know.

230
00:19:00.641 --> 00:19:02.474
but guess we gotta get used to it.
you know?

231
00:19:02.558 --> 00:19:04.974
- Global warming...
- Could you stop talking?

232
00:19:05.057 --> 00:19:06.307
Yeah.

233
00:19:06.391 --> 00:19:08.599
Please. let me get the elevator for you.
Just one sec.

234
00:19:11.474 --> 00:19:13.182
All right there. Mrs. Rooney.

235
00:19:13.266 --> 00:19:15.932
Well. try not to get lost down there.
It can be pretty confusing.

236
00:19:16.015 --> 00:19:17.974
I mean. even for me.
and I'm here every day.

237
00:19:18.057 --> 00:19:19.848
- Going down.
- Keep an eye on you!

238
00:19:19.932 --> 00:19:21.516
Fifty-two years...

239
00:19:35.140 --> 00:19:36.558
Sub-level one.

240
00:20:21.516 --> 00:20:23.099
Happy anniversary.

241
00:20:31.432 --> 00:20:32.432
Okay.

242
00:20:47.015 --> 00:20:48.140
Maybe...

243
00:20:52.391 --> 00:20:53.723
Maybe. first...

244
00:20:54.932 --> 00:20:56.015
we'll have a nap.

245
00:21:03.848 --> 00:21:06.015
<i>Feeling unhappy. stressed.</i>

246
00:21:06.099 --> 00:21:08.307
<i>and exhausted as a result</i>

247
00:21:08.391 --> 00:21:10.140
<i>of constantly putting...</i>

248
00:21:10.224 --> 00:21:12.723
<i>other people's priorities
ahead of yours...</i>

249
00:21:41.723 --> 00:21:43.890
Sorry. Hello.

250
00:21:43.974 --> 00:21:47.140
Can I get your opinion
on something? Real quick?

251
00:21:48.723 --> 00:21:49.932
Sorry again.

252
00:21:52.807 --> 00:21:54.974
So. what? You just started
picking up shifts this week

