00:21:55.057 --> 00:21:56.307
or...

254
00:21:57.432 --> 00:21:58.432
Sorry.

255
00:22:01.932 --> 00:22:03.723
Yeah. it's a pretty shit job.
you know.

256
00:22:03.807 --> 00:22:05.640
but whatever.

257
00:22:06.807 --> 00:22:08.640
Discount on storage.

258
00:22:09.932 --> 00:22:11.558
I got a lot of thoughts
on that though.

259
00:22:11.640 --> 00:22:12.765
Basically. don't do it.

260
00:22:12.848 --> 00:22:15.391
Hanging onto all your shit forever?

261
00:22:15.474 --> 00:22:17.307
It's a really terrible idea.

262
00:22:18.640 --> 00:22:21.266
This whole industry is a racket.
It's like crack.

263
00:22:21.932 --> 00:22:24.140
You just keep piling more
and more shit in there.

264
00:22:24.224 --> 00:22:26.057
and pretty soon.
you can't throw anything out...

265
00:22:26.140 --> 00:22:27.516
I don't hear anything.

266
00:22:27.598 --> 00:22:28.807
Well. I definitely heard it.

267
00:22:29.432 --> 00:22:31.099
Well. not definitely.
I mean. I was. like.

268
00:22:31.182 --> 00:22:33.349
I don't know. aware of it.
you know what I mean?

269
00:22:33.432 --> 00:22:35.516
Like. I was having an argument
with my brain about it.

270
00:22:36.432 --> 00:22:37.974
Does that ever happen to you?

271
00:22:39.057 --> 00:22:40.932
You are very chatty.

272
00:22:41.015 --> 00:22:42.099
Yeah. I know.

273
00:22:42.848 --> 00:22:44.391
It can be a problem.

274
00:22:47.015 --> 00:22:50.682
- I'm Teacake.
- Teacake.

275
00:22:50.765 --> 00:22:52.266
You must have loved that book.

276
00:22:53.391 --> 00:22:54.391
What book?

277
00:22:54.474 --> 00:22:56.932
You're named after
a famous character from a book.

278
00:22:58.765 --> 00:22:59.848
No. that ain't it.

279
00:23:01.307 --> 00:23:03.640
Long story. Fairly annoying.

280
00:23:12.307 --> 00:23:13.307
What?

281
00:23:15.682 --> 00:23:18.099
I said I do not want to hear it.

282
00:23:18.182 --> 00:23:20.848
- Listen. I've got a problem...
- Yeah. well. you always have a problem.

283
00:23:21.932 --> 00:23:23.307
- I've gotta go.
- Don't hang up on...

284
00:23:28.182 --> 00:23:30.474
Long story. Fairly annoying.

285
00:23:30.557 --> 00:23:31.640
Yeah.

286
00:23:32.557 --> 00:23:33.640
I'm Naomi.

287
00:23:36.682 --> 00:23:37.807
Nice to meet you.

288
00:23:44.307 --> 00:23:46.557
- See what I'm saying?
- Yeah.

289
00:24:06.515 --> 00:24:09.932
Hello? Hello?

290
00:24:10.015 --> 00:24:12.807
I'm calling about
the 1978 Plymouth Duster for sale.

291
00:24:16.807 --> 00:24:19.182
- Are you there?
- Give me five minutes.

292
00:24:24.266 --> 00:24:27.140
- Who was that?
- My other wife.

293
00:24:27.224 --> 00:24:29.765
How can you be funny right away
in the middle of the night?

294
00:24:29.848 --> 00:24:30.932
It's a gift.

295
00:24:32.057 --> 00:24:35.266
- One of the kids?
- No. new voice.

296
00:24:35.349 --> 00:24:36.515
I'm sure it's nothing.

297
00:24:36.598 --> 00:24:38.640
Somebody having a panic attack.

298
00:24:39.974 --> 00:24:41.099
Get back to sleep.

299
00:24:51.807 --> 00:24:53.140
You wanna call Griffin?

300
00:24:53.224 --> 00:24:55.682
Under no circumstance
do I wanna call Griffin.

301
00:24:58.140 --> 00:24:59.473
He tried that shit on you already?

302
00:25:00.598 --> 00:25:02.224
He's a pig. Pigs do.

303
00:25:02.307 --> 00:25:04.723
Damn. call the office.
Get his ass fired.

304
00:25:04.807 --> 00:25:07.640
It won't play out that way.
and I need the job.

305
00:25:07.723 --> 00:25:09.807
He ask you to flip those TVs
he racked yet?

306
00:25:11.182 --> 00:25:12.598
That has not come up.

307
00:25:12.682 --> 00:25:14.057
Oh. it will. Trust me.

308
00:25:14.807 --> 00:25:18.473
He's got. like. a million of 'em stashed
in a couple units. up there. downstairs.

309
00:25:19.640 --> 00:25:21.266
That.

310
00:25:28.974 --> 00:25:30.723
