- Maybe it's a smoke alarm.

332
00:26:34.515 --> 00:26:37.182
but maybe it's something terrible.

333
00:26:37.807 --> 00:26:40.390
I mean. we're guards. right?
We're supposed to guard the place.

334
00:26:40.473 --> 00:26:42.932
Yeah.
You know. I need this job too.

335
00:26:43.015 --> 00:26:44.598
You're not gonna lose it.

336
00:26:44.682 --> 00:26:47.306
No. you don't understand.
Like. I have to have this job.

337
00:26:47.390 --> 00:26:48.598
I get it.

338
00:26:48.682 --> 00:26:51.099
No. you don't.
I mean. it's like a condition.

339
00:26:51.182 --> 00:26:54.140
I said I get it.
I've lived here all my life.

340
00:26:54.932 --> 00:26:56.182
I know what a parole condition is.

341
00:26:56.266 --> 00:27:00.431
and I know where black-and-gray tattoos
with shitty ballpoint ink get done.

342
00:27:01.099 --> 00:27:02.515
Ellsworth. right?

343
00:27:03.515 --> 00:27:05.015
I mean. I'm hoping it was Ellsworth.

344
00:27:06.099 --> 00:27:07.348
Yeah. it was.

345
00:27:07.431 --> 00:27:09.473
Great!
So. you're not violent.

346
00:27:09.557 --> 00:27:13.974
Now. will you go and get the claw bar
and smash through that wall for me?

347
00:27:16.974 --> 00:27:18.057
Please?

348
00:27:45.598 --> 00:27:49.765
- Go ahead.
- 0474. Blue indigo. What's up?

349
00:27:49.848 --> 00:27:52.473
We're getting a temperature-breach alert
from a decommissioned facility

350
00:27:52.557 --> 00:27:54.640
in the Atchison mines
in eastern Kansas.

351
00:27:56.640 --> 00:27:59.848
Yeah. I wondered about that.
given the weather changes.

352
00:27:59.932 --> 00:28:04.057
I wrote a memo in 2007
on that very subject.

353
00:28:04.140 --> 00:28:05.890
I don't see it in the file.

354
00:28:05.974 --> 00:28:08.390
And I called about five years after that.

355
00:28:08.473 --> 00:28:11.848
And again two years ago.
What time did the alert come in?

356
00:28:11.932 --> 00:28:15.723
- 3:14 p.m. Central Standard Time.
- And you're just calling me now?

357
00:28:15.807 --> 00:28:17.515
It took some time
to figure out who to call.

358
00:28:19.723 --> 00:28:22.932
Okay.
I'm 73 miles from Seymour Johnson.

359
00:28:23.015 --> 00:28:24.723
I can be there in 90 minutes.

360
00:28:24.807 --> 00:28:26.682
I need a plane from there

361
00:28:26.765 --> 00:28:28.932
and a car waiting on the other end.

362
00:28:29.015 --> 00:28:31.598
Is it your opinion
this qualifies as a Heightened Threat?

363
00:28:31.682 --> 00:28:36.515
My opinion is it qualified
as an Exceptional Threat at 3:14 p.m.

364
00:28:36.598 --> 00:28:37.682
I'll see what I can do about...

365
00:28:37.765 --> 00:28:39.015
