379
00:29:19.348 --> 00:29:21.807
Just your first one.
even a fake one.

380
00:29:22.932 --> 00:29:24.306
something to call you.

381
00:29:25.765 --> 00:29:26.848
Abigail.

382
00:29:26.932 --> 00:29:28.181
Okay. Abigail.

383
00:29:29.348 --> 00:29:31.515
Remember those good grades
you got in high school?

384
00:29:32.181 --> 00:29:34.223
And the sports
you trained your ass off for?

385
00:29:35.015 --> 00:29:36.932
The college you fought to get into?

386
00:29:37.932 --> 00:29:41.682
Remember the abuse you put up with
your first year in the department?

387
00:29:42.390 --> 00:29:45.515
And the personal life you've given up
for the last. I don't know.

388
00:29:46.139 --> 00:29:49.598
from your voice. it sounds
like maybe 10. 12 years now?

389
00:29:50.306 --> 00:29:53.598
- Nine.
- Nine. All those sacrifices.

390
00:29:53.682 --> 00:29:56.473
all the shit you've had to eat
because you wanted to do

391
00:29:56.557 --> 00:29:58.057
what was right for your country.

392
00:29:59.181 --> 00:30:00.348
This is what it was for.

393
00:30:01.306 --> 00:30:03.306
It's worse
than you can possibly imagine.

394
00:30:04.181 --> 00:30:07.139
We are at Pucker Factor Ten. Abigail.

395
00:30:08.181 --> 00:30:10.265
But you and I are gonna sort this shit.

396
00:30:11.265 --> 00:30:12.348
Sounds good?

397
00:30:14.723 --> 00:30:15.723
Yes.

398
00:30:16.807 --> 00:30:19.015
- Yes. sir.
- Get the stuff on the list.

399
00:30:20.015 --> 00:30:21.807
I'll be at Seymour in 90 minutes.

400
00:30:27.890 --> 00:30:29.390
A whole bunch of stuff back here.

401
00:30:32.723 --> 00:30:33.723
Sorry.

402
00:30:35.181 --> 00:30:38.098
- What's that say?
- I gotta get a closer look.

403
00:30:39.431 --> 00:30:40.431
Sorry.

404
00:30:45.348 --> 00:30:48.265
NTC. Thermistor Breach.

405
00:30:49.265 --> 00:30:51.139
Hold on. give me a second.

406
00:30:53.807 --> 00:30:55.139
Oh. my God! Are you okay?

407
00:30:55.682 --> 00:30:57.932
Yep! Planned that.

408
00:31:05.015 --> 00:31:07.598
Airtight Integrity. yeah.

409
00:31:07.682 --> 00:31:10.515
plus or minus 0.1 degree Celsius.

410
00:31:12.139 --> 00:31:15.014
Cold Chain Synchronicity.
Jesus. there's. like. 20 of them.

411
00:31:16.265 --> 00:31:17.765
But that's the only one that's blinking.

412
00:31:17.848 --> 00:31:21.348
- NTC. Thermistor Breach.
- What's it do?

413
00:31:21.431 --> 00:31:24.223
Well. a thermistor is part
of an electrical circuit.

414
00:31:24.306 --> 00:31:26.932
There are two kinds.
the positive kind

415
00:31:27.014 --> 00:31:28.682
where resistance rises
with temperature.

416
00:31:28.765 --> 00:31:31.515
and the negative kind
where the resistance falls

417
00:31:31.598 --> 00:31:32.765
when the temperature goes up.

418
00:31:33.765 --> 00:31:35.723
So. like a thermometer?

419
00:31:35.807 --> 00:31:39.431
No. like a circuit
that's reactive to temperature.

420
00:31:40.932 --> 00:31:42.807
- Like a thermometer?
- It's not a thermometer.

421
00:31:43.848 --> 00:31:45.181
What?
Are you all science-y and shit?

422
00:31:45.265 --> 00:31:47.348
Well. I wouldn't say. and shit.

423
00:31:47.431 --> 00:31:50.682
Take a lot of science.
prerequisite for vet school.

424
00:32:01.056 --> 00:32:04.848
Hey! Wha...
